<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 03 at 3:36AM EST  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Moore,
Montgomery, northwestern Richmond, southern Randolph, southeastern
Stanly and southwestern Chatham Counties through 400 AM EST...
At 334 AM EST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southwest of Troy, moving northeast at 85 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Asheboro, Randleman, Troy, North Carolina Zoo, Biscoe, Seagrove,
Norwood, Ramseur, Mount Gilead and Franklinville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>Seek shelter inside a strong building.</instruction>
